&lt;p&gt;Prior to commencement of development details of soundproofing between the ground floor use hereby approved and the residential use at first floor shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The neighbouring residential use shall receive a minimum airborne sound insulation on the party element which achieves DnT&#x27;w of 60 dB.&amp;nbsp; The sound installation shall be installed in accordance with the approved details prior to the commencement of use and be retained thereafter in perpetuity.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
REASON: To ensure that neighbouring occupiers do not suffer a loss of amenity by reason of noise nuisance and other excess noise from activities within the premises
&lt;/p&gt;
